          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Reactor neutron spectrum, neutron flux = 3x10**12",
                "n/cm2/sec.",
                "- Comment: for Th-232 (fission threshold 1 MeV) the",
                "  fission neutron part of the spectrum is relevant.",
                "Comment by compiler: The neutron energy is not given",
                "explicitely but the reactor type and the neutrons being",
                "referred to as 'reactor neutrons' indicate that the",
                "spectrum is that of a thermal reactor. However, (see",
                "subentry 3) the U-235 yields are normalized to the",
                "Ce-140 fast fission yield of Lisman et al, and in the",
                "publication, all yields are compared to fast fission",
                "yields by other authors. At least the normalization and",
                "the neutron energy should be checked before using",
                "absolute values of these yields."
              ]
            }
          ],
